United Capital Plc recorded significant growths in incomes and profitability in the first quarter as the investment and finance group grew net earnings by 39 per cent. Key extracts of the interim report and accounts for the three-month period ended March 31, 2022 showed that gross earnings rose by 35 per cent while pre and post tax profits grew by 36 per cent and 39 per cent. Underlying ratios indicated that the outward performance was driven by improvement in the intrinsic operations of the group. Pre-tax profit margin improved from 63.29 per cent in first quarter 2021 to 63.81 per cent in first quarter 2022. Net profit margin also increased from 53.1 per cent to 54.81 per cent. Gross earnings rose to N4.21 billion in first quarter 2022 as against N3.12 billion in comparable period of 2021. Net operating income grew by 14 per cent to N3.55 billion in 2022 compared with N3.10 billion in 2021. Operating expenses however rose by 44 per cent from N1.15 billion to N1.64 billion. Profit before tax stood at N2.69 billion in first quarter 2022 as against N1.97 billion in first quarter 2021. After taxes, net profit rose from N1.66 billion in first quarter 2021 to N2.31 billion in first quarter 2022. 		 			Military mops up 517 weapons in Plateau, Kaduna, Bauchi		 		 		 			Driver knocks, kills LASTMA officer to evade arrest		 		 		 			Insecurity: Obasanjo canvasses state police		 		 The balance sheet of the group also emerged stronger during the period. Total assets expanded to N463.93 billion by March 2022 compared with  N453.60 billion recorded at the beginning of the year. Total liabilities stood at N440.08 billion by first quarter 2022 as against N423.05 billion posted at the end of the 2021 financial year. Group Chief Executive Officer, United Capital Plc, Mr. Peter Ashade, said United Capital is on a sustainable growth trajectory driven by increasing patronage and expanded activities across all its businesses, and market segments. He noted that as a financial market player, capital market operator, investment manager, and consumer lender, the group plays a unique role in expanding service offerings in the financial services ecosystem while creating and distributing wealth amongst diverse stakeholders. “We kicked-off the year 2022 on a sure footing and we are poised to deliver new services and expand into new markets to grow our businesses in line with our three-year growth strategy,” Ashade said. Chairman, United Capital Plc, Prof. Chika Mordi, said the group is on a remarkable growth path as reflected in its strong financial results in first quarter 2022. “We remain uniquely positioned to increasing value delivery to all our stakeholders,” Mordi said.